🤖 Week 2: AI Automation, Webhooks, & Beta Launch
Day 8: Standardizing the Python LLM Hook
Focus: Senior Developer Engine
Tasks:
[ ] Install the official pipeline package library for your chosen AI infrastructure model via pip (openai or anthropic).
[ ] Store your operational secure API tokens safely within your project configuration layers.
[ ] Write an independent Python helper script inside your architecture that sends text to the chat completions API endpoint and returns responses smoothly.
🎯 Milestone: A basic terminal script execution confirms that your code can reliably exchange raw text data packages directly with an advanced language model parser.
Day 9: The Webhook Receiver Core
Focus: Event Interception
Tasks:
[ ] Open up a custom public URL path view endpoint specifically configured to handle external server calls (/webhooks/github/).
[ ] Write logic to catch POST requests and parse incoming GitHub JSON transaction headers securely.
[ ] Set up ngrok or a standard localhost tunnel proxy server locally on your workstation to expose your development port to the wider web.
🎯 Milestone: Altering status elements or pushing test commits inside GitHub triggers a visible print event tracking block output log print inside your local Django server logs.
Day 10: Structuring the Code Review Script
Focus: Evaluation Quality
Tasks:
[ ] Refine your webhook view logic to extract the raw pull request code diff strings from incoming text feeds.
[ ] Craft a clean system prompt instructing the model to evaluate the incoming diff against the avatar validation bug rubric.
[ ] Pass the payload securely to the AI API wrapper and map the return text arrays explicitly back to clean markdown variables.
🎯 Milestone: Your script captures pull request diff variations and successfully maps them directly to conversational engineering critiques.
Day 11: Hooking Up the Automation Circuit
Focus: Automated Workflow Loop
Tasks:
[ ] Connect your webhook endpoint directly to your evaluation model logic loop.
[ ] Set up data triggers to instantiate an AISubmissionReview record automatically upon receiving any foreign pull request payload.
[ ] Program conditional flag parsing logic: if the LLM output explicitly determines a passing condition met, automatically flip the TicketAssignment status fields directly over to DONE.
🎯 Milestone: Submitting an operational pull request update instantly adjusts user project columns on the main site platform interface layout without typing manual dashboard commands.
Day 12: Markdown Rendering & Visual Cleanups
Focus: Interface Polish
Tasks:
[ ] Implement a basic markdown-to-HTML parser extension filter directly within your template file configuration layers.
[ ] Build the custom review report overview screen template layout (/backlog/review/<id>/).
[ ] Style the output container layout to neatly mirror a live code review pull request review page thread.
🎯 Milestone: Highly granular code reviews display cleanly as polished, readable technical documentation tabs on your web portal interface.
Day 13: Adversarial Verification Testing
Focus: Edge-Case Robustness
Tasks:
[ ] Execute a flawed, quick-fix resolution patch against the cloud repo to see if the evaluation model flags systemic oversights or hard-coded shortcuts.
[ ] Refine the evaluation prompt guidelines if the code checking parameters fail to flag structural oversights effectively.
[ ] Verify error tracking pipelines perform correctly if external API communication loops drop out intermittently.
🎯 Milestone: Your AI reliably catches quick, low-quality code patches while safely approving deep structural fixes.
